</problem></exercise>

      <exercise id="fs-id1169737961204" type="conceptual-questions">
        <problem id="fs-id1169738173849">
    <para id="import-auto-id1169736581603">Can the lines in a diffraction grating be too close together to be useful as a spectroscopic tool for visible light? If so, what type of EM radiation would the grating be suitable for? Explain.</para>
