      <exercise id="fs-id1169738256769" type="problems-exercises">
        <problem id="fs-id1169738164427">
          <para id="import-auto-id1169737733776">An electric current through hydrogen gas produces several distinct wavelengths of visible light. What are the wavelengths of the hydrogen spectrum, if they form first-order maxima at angles of <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mtext>24</m:mtext><m:mtext>.</m:mtext><m:mn>2º</m:mn></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{"24" "." 2°} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math>, <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mtext>25</m:mtext><m:mtext>.</m:mtext><m:mn>7º</m:mn></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{"25" "." 7°} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math>, <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mtext>29</m:mtext><m:mtext>.</m:mtext><m:mn>1º</m:mn></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{"29" "." 1°} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math>, and <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mtext>41</m:mtext><m:mtext>.</m:mtext><m:mn>0º</m:mn></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{"41" "." 0°} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> when projected on a diffraction grating having 10,000 lines per centimeter? Explicitly show how you follow the steps in <link document="m42519" target-id="fs-id1169737988256">Problem-Solving Strategies for Wave Optics</link></para></problem></exercise>

