  <glossary>
    <definition id="import-auto-id1169738211584"><term>constructive interference for a diffraction grating</term> <meaning id="fs-id1169738137919">occurs when the condition <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mo fontstyle="italic">d</m:mo><m:mspace width="0.25em"/><m:mtext>sin</m:mtext><m:mspace width="0.25em"/><m:mrow><m:mi>θ</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo><m:mi fontstyle="italic">mλ</m:mi></m:mrow><m:mspace width="0.25em"/><m:mrow><m:mtext>(for </m:mtext><m:mspace width="0.25em"/><m:mi>m</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo><m:mtext>0,</m:mtext></m:mrow><m:mspace width="0.25em"/><m:mtext>1,</m:mtext><m:mspace width="0.25em"/><m:mtext>–1,</m:mtext><m:mspace width="0.25em"/><m:mtext>2,</m:mtext><m:mspace width="0.25em"/><m:mtext>–2,</m:mtext><m:mspace width="0.25em"/><m:mo stretchy="false">…)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow></m:semantics></m:math> is satisfied, where <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>d</m:mi></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{d} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> is the distance between slits in the grating, <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>λ</m:mi></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{λ} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> is the wavelength of light, and <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>m</m:mi></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{m} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> is the order of the maximum</meaning></definition>
    <definition id="import-auto-id1169737968833"><term>diffraction grating</term> <meaning id="fs-id1169736739815">a large number of evenly spaced parallel slits</meaning></definition>
  </glossary>
